article.headline: Norfolk St. 81, Longwood 74
article.story: FARMVILLE, Va. -- Corey Lyons scored 25 points and Michael Deloach notched a double-double to help Norfolk State hold off Longwood 81-74 on Sunday night. Deloach scored 19 points and grabbed 13 rebounds for the Spartans (1-0), who are now 2-0 in season openers under coach Anthony Evans. He also had a team-high eight assists. Lyons was 6-for-8 from behind the arc. Ryan Bogan led the Lancers (1-1) with 20 points, and Dana Smith recorded a double-double with 16 points and 15 rebounds. Bogan also chipped in seven rebounds. The Spartans overcame 23 turnovers by shooting 52.9 percent (27 of 51) from the field for the game, and making 17 of 19 free throws. The Lancers shot 39.9 percent (29 of 73) in the contest.
